Waterloo.Waterloo East High School:
East High School in Waterloo, Iowa is a public high school consisting of approximately 1000 students in grades 9-12.


== History ==
The school was founded at its current site in 1874, with the present building being built in 1918. In 1939, the Music and Industrial Arts wing was added, and the Fred J. Miller gymnasium was built in 1957.
